{"key":"post-12725101","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12725101</id>\n<content>You pick fruits as they're ready.&amp;nbsp; Try not to damage nearby pins as that can cause them to abort.&amp;nbsp; If you're picking from a densely fruiting substrate, carefully snip the stems near the base with a sharp knife or scissors, and then remove the stubs when you pick the rest of the flush.&amp;nbsp; This will minimize damage to still-growing fruits.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12725035</prev>\n<first>12719664</first>\n<last>12725101</last>\n<when>1276265940</when>\n<utime>06/11/10 05:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}